\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 Each case presented here includes as an important element some basic attitude or attitudes popular in our own society. In the possessed person, it is pushed to a narrow and frightening extreme.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 In the first case,\~Zio\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s Friend and the Smiler, the insistence is that there is no essential difference between good and evil, and ultimately no difference between being and nonbeing; that all values are subject only to one\u8217\'92s personal preferences.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 In\~Father Bones and Mister Natch, the compelling idea that was seized by Evil Spirit seemed to be that all mysteries can and are resolved in \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93natural\u8221\'94 (i.e., rational or scientific or quantifiable) explanations; that there can be no relevance for the modern person in\~}{\f0\fs24\b0 a}{\f0\fs24\b0 nything that cannot be rationally understood; and that there can be no truth important to man beyond what is rational.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 In\~The Virgin and the Girl-Fixer, the battle concerned some of the great, deep, and mysterious \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93givens\u8221\'94 of our very nature and our society\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 in this case, gender and human love. The priest in this case said to me a few months before he died, in one of the most profound conversations of my life: \u8220\'93A bird doesn\u8217\'92t fly because it has wings. It has wings because it flies.\u8221\'94 We will ignore that mysterious truth in its applications to our sexuality and our gender only at our great peril, I believe.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 In\~Uncle Ponto and the Mushroom-Souper, we have an example of what may be happening to many in our modern society\hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0 without their realizing it and without those around them taking cognizance of it. For it seems that there is an individualism, a purely personalistic interpretation of human life abroad today, which exceeds by far the bounds of what used to be known as selfishness and egotism. It has produced in thousands of people an aberrant and idiosyncratic behavior which is truly destructive.}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0 In\~The Rooster and the Tortoise, the fatal confusion (and in this case it was literally almost fatal) was between spirit and psyche; between those parts and attributes of ours that are quantifiable, and yet through which spirit most easily makes itself known. If everything we have taken to be of spirit can be made to seem a product merely of the human psyche, with no meaning or significance beyond its factualness, then love can be made to seem only a chemical interraction, and love\loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8217\'92s paradigm is killed.}
